DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Hey newbie! The doctor asked me to come with you so you don’t get lost down there!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: May

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Do you know how to get to the plaza?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: May

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Oook, just making sure! I’ll follow you!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: You’re overflowing with confidence... Follow me!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Why haven't we left yet?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Pei!!!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I'm doing great, just showing this Noob around a bit. What are you up to?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Just getting a few supplies for the noodle stand. I'd love to talk, but I have to run. I want to make it in time for the lunch rush.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: OH man now I'm hungry. She's got the best noodles EVER!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: We have to go deeper into the Belly.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: That's the wrong way, Noobie. C'mon!
I am the new bartender. I am sorry but the bar is currently closed.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: There's the stand!! Best. Noodles. Ever!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Frank's apartment isn't this way, though...

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Stop tickling me and keep going!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Where are you going, dude? It's that way, down the alleyway!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Here we are! This is Frank's apartment.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Stupid! This is what we came for. The door's right here.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Looks like the big guy was in a hurry, huh?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I guess you'll have to do your job and find something...

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Hurry up Noobie. Why are you taking so long?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Hi Frank! Please say your security word to continue!

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: PEIJUN is a very nice woman, and her noodles are delicious.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I just heard yelling coming the ROOM NEXT DOOR, and I feel it's got something to do with my recent investifation.
